<paragraph blockId="1.[170,776,1750,1997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">
Coloniae amphigenae, subdensae, ad 
<quantity box="[640,693,1910,1933]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="2.0">2mm</quantity>
diam., confluentes. Hyphae subrectae vel anfractuae, opposite vel irregulariter acuteque vel laxe ramosae, laxe vel arte
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[812,1387,809,874]" box="[812,1387,833,851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">a - Appressorium; b - Phialide; c - Apical portion of the mycelial setae;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[812,1387,809,874]" box="[812,936,856,874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">d - Ascospores</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1424,917,1932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">
reticulatae, cellulae 12-32 x 
<quantity box="[1100,1174,917,940]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4-8 µm</quantity>
. Appressoria opposita, alternata, unilateralis, antrorsa, subantrorsa vel retrorsa, recta vel curvula, 
<quantity box="[1025,1133,981,1004]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="11.0">11-26 µm</quantity>
longa; cellulae basilares cylindraceae vel cuneatae, 
<quantity box="[1090,1162,1013,1036]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3-8 µm</quantity>
longae; cellulae apicales oblongae, ovatae, cylindraceae, globosae, rectae vel varie curvulae, integrae vel angularis, 8-18 x 
<quantity box="[1212,1303,1077,1100]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="6.0">6-15 µm</quantity>
. Phialides appressoriis intermixtae, oppositae vel alternatae, ampulliformes, 16-24 x 
<quantity box="[1050,1124,1141,1164]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6-8 µm</quantity>
. Setae myceliales simplices, rectae, ad apicem acutae, ad 
<quantity box="[1144,1216,1173,1196]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="490.0">490µm</quantity>
longae. Perithecia dispersa vel aggregata, ad 
<quantity box="[1127,1200,1205,1228]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="160.0">160µm</quantity>
diam.; ascosporae obovoideae, 4-septatae, leniter constrictus ad septatae, 38-45 x 
<quantity box="[905,1009,1269,1292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12-16 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1424,917,1932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">
Colonies amphigenous, subdense, up to 
<quantity box="[1330,1383,1301,1324]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="2.0">2mm</quantity>
in diameter, confluent. Hyphae substraight to crooked, branching opposite to irregular at acute to wide angles, loosely to closely reticulate, cells 12-32 x 
<quantity box="[1325,1414,1397,1420]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4-8 µm</quantity>
. Appressoria opposite, alternate, unilateral, antrorse, subantrorse to retrorse, straight to curved, 
<quantity box="[1260,1360,1461,1484]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="11.0">11-26 µm</quantity>
long; stalk cells cylindrical to cuneate, 
<quantity box="[1165,1241,1493,1516]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3-8 µm</quantity>
long; head cells oblong, ovate, cylindrical, globose, straight to variously curved, entire to angular, 8-18 x 
<quantity box="[1147,1237,1557,1580]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="6.0">6-15 µm</quantity>
. Phialides mixed with appressoria, opposite to alternate, ampulliform, 16- 24 x 
<quantity box="[863,941,1621,1644]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6-8 µm</quantity>
. Mycelial setae, simple, straight, acute at the tip, up to 
<quantity box="[907,981,1653,1676]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="490.0">490µm</quantity>
long. Perithecia scattered to grouped, up to 
<quantity box="[841,915,1685,1708]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="160.0">160µm</quantity>
in diameter; ascospores obovoidal, 4-septate, slightly constricted at the septa, 38-45 x 
<quantity box="[1241,1346,1717,1740]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12-16 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1424,917,1932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">
Crooked mycelium with variously curved appressoria with cylindrical to oblong head cells distinguishes this species from rest of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1088,1256,1813,1836]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1088,1164,1813,1836]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="890">Meliola</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
known on the members of the family 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1218,1845,1868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ebenaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansford, C. G." box="[1241,1414,1845,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" pagination="1 - 806" refId="ref2067" refString="Hansford, C. G. (1961). The Meliolaceae. A Monograph. Sydowia Beih 2: 1 - 806." type="journal article" year="1961">Hansford 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hosagoudar, V. B. &amp; T. K. Abraham &amp; P. Pushpangadan" box="[813,1060,1877,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" refId="ref2115" refString="Hosagoudar, V. B., T. K. Abraham &amp; P. Pushpangadan (1997). The Meliolineae - A Supplement. Tropical Botanic Garden and Research Institute, Palode, Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala, India, 201 pp." type="book" year="1997">Hosagoudar et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
; Hu et al. 1997, 1999; Hosagoudar 2008; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hosagoudar, V. B. &amp; D. K. Agarwal" box="[879,1190,1909,1932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="890" refId="ref2184" refString="Hosagoudar, V. B. &amp; D. K. Agarwal (2008). Taxonomic studies of Meliolales. Identification Manual. International Book Distributors, Dehradun, 263 pp." type="book" year="2008">Hosagoudar &amp; Agarwal 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
